acceptCall.desc:
Accepts an incoming call.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Call identifier.
fields.name: call_id

fields.desc: The call protocols supported by the application.
fields.name: protocol

acceptTermsOfService.desc:
Accepts Telegram terms of services.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Terms of service identifier.
fields.name: terms_of_service_id

activateStoryStealthMode.desc:
Activates stealth mode for stories, which hides all views of stories from the current user in the last "story_stealth_mode_past_period" seconds and for the next "story_stealth_mode_future_period" seconds; for Telegram Premium users only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

addApplicationChangelog.desc:
Adds server-provided application changelog as messages to the chat 777000 (Telegram) or as a stories; for official applications only. Returns a 404 error if nothing changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The previous application version.
fields.name: previous_application_version

addChatFolderByInviteLink.desc:
Adds a chat folder by an invite link.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Invite link for the chat folder.
fields.name: invite_link

fields.desc: Identifiers of the chats added to the chat folder. The chats are automatically joined if they aren't joined yet.
fields.name: chat_ids

addChatMember.desc:
Adds a new member to a chat. Members can't be added to private or secret chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the user.
fields.name: user_id

fields.desc: The number of earlier messages from the chat to be forwarded to the new member; up to 100. Ignored for supergroups and channels, or if the added user is a bot.
fields.name: forward_limit

addChatMembers.desc:
Adds multiple new members to a chat. Currently, this method is only available for supergroups and channels. This method can't be used to join a chat. Members can't be added to a channel if it has more than 200 members.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat. The maximum number of added users is 20 for supergroups and 100 for channels.
fields.name: user_ids

addChatToList.desc:
Adds a chat to a chat list. A chat can't be simultaneously in Main and Archive chat lists, so it is automatically removed from another one if needed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: The chat list. Use getChatListsToAddChat to get suitable chat lists.
fields.name: chat_list

addContact.desc:
Adds a user to the contact list or edits an existing contact by their user identifier.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The contact to add or edit; phone number may be empty and needs to be specified only if known, vCard is ignored.
fields.name: contact

fields.desc: Pass true to share the current user's phone number with the new contact. A corresponding rule to userPrivacySettingShowPhoneNumber will be added if needed. Use the field userFullInfo.need_phone_number_privacy_exception to check whether the current user needs to be asked to share their phone number.
fields.name: share_phone_number

addCustomServerLanguagePack.desc:
Adds a custom server language pack to the list of installed language packs in current localization target. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of a language pack to be added.
fields.name: language_pack_id

addFavoriteSticker.desc:
Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list. Emoji stickers can't be added to favorite stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Sticker file to add.
fields.name: sticker

addFileToDownloads.desc:
Adds a file from a message to the list of file downloads. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates. If message database is used, the list of file downloads is persistent across application restarts. The downloading is independent from download using downloadFile, i.e. it continues if downloadFile is canceled or is used to download a part of the file.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the file to download.
fields.name: file_id

fields.desc: Chat identifier of the message with the file.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Message identifier.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first.
fields.name: priority

addLocalMessage.desc:
Adds a local message to a chat. The message is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used. Returns the added message.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: Target chat.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the sender of the message.
fields.name: sender_id

fields.desc: Information about the message or story to be replied; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_to

fields.desc: Pass true to disable notification for the message.
fields.name: disable_notification

fields.desc: The content of the message to be added.
fields.name: input_message_content

addLogMessage.desc:
Adds a message to TDLib internal log. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The minimum verbosity level needed for the message to be logged; 0-1023.
fields.name: verbosity_level

fields.desc: Text of a message to log.
fields.name: text

addMessageReaction.desc:
Adds a reaction to a message. Use getMessageAvailableReactions to receive the list of available reactions for the message.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: Type of the reaction to add.
fields.name: reaction_type

fields.desc: Pass true if the reaction is added with a big animation.
fields.name: is_big

fields.desc: Pass true if the reaction needs to be added to recent reactions.
fields.name: update_recent_reactions

addNetworkStatistics.desc:
Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The network statistics entry with the data to be added to statistics.
fields.name: entry

addProxy.desc:
Adds a proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Proxy>.

fields.desc: Proxy server domain or IP address.
fields.name: server

fields.desc: Proxy server port.
fields.name: port

fields.desc: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy.
fields.name: enable

fields.desc: Proxy type.
fields.name: type

addRecentSticker.desc:
Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first. Only stickers belonging to a sticker set can be added to this list. Emoji stickers can't be added to recent stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Stickers>.

fields.desc: Pass true to add the sticker to the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to add the sticker to the list of recently sent stickers.
fields.name: is_attached

fields.desc: Sticker file to add.
fields.name: sticker

addRecentlyFoundChat.desc:
Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to add.
fields.name: chat_id

addSavedAnimation.desc:
Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first. Only non-secret video animations with MIME type "video/mp4" can be added to the list.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The animation file to be added. Only animations known to the server (i.e., successfully sent via a message) can be added to the list.
fields.name: animation

addSavedNotificationSound.desc:
Adds a new notification sound to the list of saved notification sounds. The new notification sound is added to the top of the list. If it is already in the list, its position isn't changed.
Returns object_ptr<NotificationSound>.

fields.desc: Notification sound file to add.
fields.name: sound

addStickerToSet.desc:
Adds a new sticker to a set; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Sticker set owner.
fields.name: user_id

fields.desc: Sticker set name.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Sticker to add to the set.
fields.name: sticker

allowBotToSendMessages.desc:
Allows the specified bot to send messages to the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the target bot.
fields.name: bot_user_id

answerCallbackQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the callback query.
fields.name: callback_query_id

fields.desc: Text of the answer.
fields.name: text

fields.desc: Pass true to show an alert to the user instead of a toast notification.
fields.name: show_alert

fields.desc: URL to be opened.
fields.name: url

fields.desc: Time during which the result of the query can be cached, in seconds.
fields.name: cache_time

answerCustomQuery.desc:
Answers a custom query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of a custom query.
fields.name: custom_query_id

fields.desc: JSON-serialized answer to the query.
fields.name: data

answerInlineQuery.desc:
Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the inline query.
fields.name: inline_query_id

fields.desc: Pass true if results may be cached and returned only for the user that sent the query. By default, results may be returned to any user who sends the same query.
fields.name: is_personal

fields.desc: Button to be shown above inline query results; pass null if none.
fields.name: button

fields.desc: The results of the query.
fields.name: results

fields.desc: Allowed time to cache the results of the query, in seconds.
fields.name: cache_time

fields.desc: Offset for the next inline query; pass an empty string if there are no more results.
fields.name: next_offset

answerPreCheckoutQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the pre-checkout query.
fields.name: pre_checkout_query_id

fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.
fields.name: error_message

answerShippingQuery.desc:
Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the shipping query.
fields.name: shipping_query_id

fields.desc: Available shipping options.
fields.name: shipping_options

fields.desc: An error message, empty on success.
fields.name: error_message

answerWebAppQuery.desc:
Sets the result of interaction with a Web App and sends corresponding message on behalf of the user to the chat from which the query originated; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<SentWebAppMessage>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the Web App query.
fields.name: web_app_query_id

fields.desc: The result of the query.
fields.name: result

applyPremiumGiftCode.desc:
Applies a Telegram Premium gift code.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The code to apply.
fields.name: code

assignAppStoreTransaction.desc:
Informs server about a purchase through App Store. For official applications only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: App Store receipt.
fields.name: receipt

fields.desc: Transaction purpose.
fields.name: purpose

assignGooglePlayTransaction.desc:
Informs server about a purchase through Google Play. For official applications only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Application package name.
fields.name: package_name

fields.desc: Identifier of the purchased store product.
fields.name: store_product_id

fields.desc: Google Play purchase token.
fields.name: purchase_token

fields.desc: Transaction purpose.
fields.name: purpose

banChatMember.desc:
Bans a member in a chat. Members can't be banned in private or secret chats. In supergroups and channels, the user will not be able to return to the group on their own using invite links, etc., unless unbanned first.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Member identifier.
fields.name: member_id

fields.desc: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the user will be unbanned; 0 if never. If the user is banned for more than 366 days or for less than 30 seconds from the current time, the user is considered to be banned forever. Ignored in basic groups and if a chat is banned.
fields.name: banned_until_date

fields.desc: Pass true to delete all messages in the chat for the user that is being removed. Always true for supergroups and channels.
fields.name: revoke_messages

blockMessageSenderFromReplies.desc:
Blocks an original sender of a message in the Replies chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The identifier of an incoming message in the Replies chat.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: Pass true to delete the message.
fields.name: delete_message

fields.desc: Pass true to delete all messages from the same sender.
fields.name: delete_all_messages

fields.desc: Pass true to report the sender to the Telegram moderators.
fields.name: report_spam

boostChat.desc:
Boosts a chat and returns the list of available chat boost slots for the current user after the boost.
Returns object_ptr<ChatBoostSlots>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of boost slots of the current user from which to apply boosts to the chat.
fields.name: slot_ids

canBotSendMessages.desc:
Checks whether the specified bot can send messages to the user. Returns a 404 error if can't and the access can be granted by call to allowBotToSendMessages.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the target bot.
fields.name: bot_user_id

canPurchasePremium.desc:
Checks whether Telegram Premium purchase is possible. Must be called before in-store Premium purchase.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Transaction purpose.
fields.name: purpose

canSendStory.desc:
Checks whether the current user can send a story on behalf of a chat; requires can_post_stories rights for channel chats.
Returns object_ptr<CanSendStoryResult>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

canTransferOwnership.desc:
Checks whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user.
Returns object_ptr<CanTransferOwnershipResult>.

cancelDownloadFile.desc:
Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of a file to stop downloading.
fields.name: file_id

fields.desc: Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn't been started, i.e. request hasn't been sent to server.
fields.name: only_if_pending

cancelPasswordReset.desc:
Cancels reset of 2-step verification password. The method can be called if passwordState.pending_reset_date > 0.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

cancelPreliminaryUploadFile.desc:
Stops the preliminary uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using preliminaryUploadFile. For other files the behavior is undefined.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the file to stop uploading.
fields.name: file_id

changeImportedContacts.desc:
Changes imported contacts using the list of contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts. Query result depends on the result of the previous query, so only one query is possible at the same time.
Returns object_ptr<ImportedContacts>.

fields.desc: The new list of contacts, contact's vCard are ignored and are not imported.
fields.name: contacts

changePhoneNumber.desc:
Changes the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user's new phone number; for official Android and iOS applications only. On success, returns information about the sent code.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

fields.desc: The new phone number of the user in international format.
fields.name: phone_number

fields.desc: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number; pass null to use default settings.
fields.name: settings

changeStickerSet.desc:
Installs/uninstalls or activates/archives a sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set.
fields.name: set_id

fields.desc: The new value of is_installed.
fields.name: is_installed

fields.desc: The new value of is_archived. A sticker set can't be installed and archived simultaneously.
fields.name: is_archived

checkAuthenticationBotToken.desc:
Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The bot token.
fields.name: token

checkAuthenticationCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Authentication code to check.
fields.name: code

checkAuthenticationEmailCode.desc:
Checks the authentication of a email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Email address authentication to check.
fields.name: code

checkAuthenticationPassword.desc:
Checks the 2-step verification password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The 2-step verification password to check.
fields.name: password

checkAuthenticationPasswordRecoveryCode.desc:
Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Recovery code to check.
fields.name: recovery_code

checkChangePhoneNumberCode.desc:
Checks the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number of the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Authentication code to check.
fields.name: code

checkChatFolderInviteLink.desc:
Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat folder and returns information about the corresponding chat folder.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFolderInviteLinkInfo>.

fields.desc: Invite link to be checked.
fields.name: invite_link

checkChatInviteLink.desc:
Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLinkInfo>.

fields.desc: Invite link to be checked.
fields.name: invite_link

checkChatUsername.desc:
Checks whether a username can be set for a chat.
Returns object_ptr<CheckChatUsernameResult>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier; must be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or 0 if the chat is being created.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Username to be checked.
fields.name: username

checkCreatedPublicChatsLimit.desc:
Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit.
fields.name: type

checkEmailAddressVerificationCode.desc:
Checks the email address verification code for Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Verification code to check.
fields.name: code

checkLoginEmailAddressCode.desc:
Checks the login email address authentication.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Email address authentication to check.
fields.name: code

checkPasswordRecoveryCode.desc:
Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Recovery code to check.
fields.name: recovery_code

checkPhoneNumberConfirmationCode.desc:
Checks phone number confirmation code.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Confirmation code to check.
fields.name: code

checkPhoneNumberVerificationCode.desc:
Checks the phone number verification code for Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Verification code to check.
fields.name: code

checkPremiumGiftCode.desc:
Return information about a Telegram Premium gift code.
Returns object_ptr<PremiumGiftCodeInfo>.

fields.desc: The code to check.
fields.name: code

checkRecoveryEmailAddressCode.desc:
Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

fields.desc: Verification code to check.
fields.name: code

checkStickerSetName.desc:
Checks whether a name can be used for a new sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<CheckStickerSetNameResult>.

fields.desc: Name to be checked.
fields.name: name

cleanFileName.desc:
Removes potentially dangerous characters from the name of a file. The encoding of the file name is supposed to be UTF-8. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously.
Returns object_ptr<Text>.

fields.desc: File name or path to the file.
fields.name: file_name

clearAllDraftMessages.desc:
Clears message drafts in all chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Pass true to keep local message drafts in secret chats.
fields.name: exclude_secret_chats

clearAutosaveSettingsExceptions.desc:
Clears the list of all autosave settings exceptions. The method is guaranteed to work only after at least one call to getAutosaveSettings.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearImportedContacts.desc:
Clears all imported contacts, contact list remains unchanged.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentEmojiStatuses.desc:
Clears the list of recently used emoji statuses.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentReactions.desc:
Clears the list of recently used reactions.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clearRecentStickers.desc:
Clears the list of recently used stickers.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Pass true to clear the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to clear the list of recently sent stickers.
fields.name: is_attached

clearRecentlyFoundChats.desc:
Clears the list of recently found chats.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

clickAnimatedEmojiMessage.desc:
Informs TDLib that a message with an animated emoji was clicked by the user. Returns a big animated sticker to be played or a 404 error if usual animation needs to be played.
Returns object_ptr<Sticker>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier of the message.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the clicked message.
fields.name: message_id

clickChatSponsoredMessage.desc:
Informs TDLib that the user opened the sponsored chat via the button, the name, the photo, or a mention in the sponsored message.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier of the sponsored message.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the sponsored message.
fields.name: message_id

clickPremiumSubscriptionButton.desc:
Informs TDLib that the user clicked Premium subscription button on the Premium features screen.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

close.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before initialization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

closeChat.desc:
Informs TDLib that the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

closeSecretChat.desc:
Closes a secret chat, effectively transferring its state to secretChatStateClosed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.
fields.name: secret_chat_id

closeStory.desc:
Informs TDLib that a story is closed by the user.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The identifier of the sender of the story to close.
fields.name: story_sender_chat_id

fields.desc: The identifier of the story.
fields.name: story_id

closeWebApp.desc:
Informs TDLib that a previously opened Web App was closed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of Web App launch, received from openWebApp.
fields.name: web_app_launch_id

confirmQrCodeAuthentication.desc:
Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success.
Returns object_ptr<Session>.

fields.desc: A link from a QR code. The link must be scanned by the in-app camera.
fields.name: link

confirmSession.desc:
Confirms an unconfirmed session of the current user from another device.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Session identifier.
fields.name: session_id

createBasicGroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Basic group identifier.
fields.name: basic_group_id

fields.desc: Pass true to create the chat without a network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.
fields.name: force

createCall.desc:
Creates a new call.
Returns object_ptr<CallId>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the user to be called.
fields.name: user_id

fields.desc: The call protocols supported by the application.
fields.name: protocol

fields.desc: Pass true to create a video call.
fields.name: is_video

createChatFolder.desc:
Creates new chat folder. Returns information about the created chat folder. There can be up to getOption("chat_folder_count_max") chat folders, but the limit can be increased with Telegram Premium.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFolderInfo>.

fields.desc: The new chat folder.
fields.name: folder

createChatFolderInviteLink.desc:
Creates a new invite link for a chat folder. A link can be created for a chat folder if it has only pinned and included chats.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFolderInviteLink>.

fields.desc: Chat folder identifier.
fields.name: chat_folder_id

fields.desc: Name of the link; 0-32 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Identifiers of chats to be accessible by the invite link. Use getChatsForChatFolderInviteLink to get suitable chats. Basic groups will be automatically converted to supergroups before link creation.
fields.name: chat_ids

createChatInviteLink.desc:
Creates a new invite link for a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLink>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Invite link name; 0-32 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the link will expire; pass 0 if never.
fields.name: expiration_date

fields.desc: The maximum number of chat members that can join the chat via the link simultaneously; 0-99999; pass 0 if not limited.
fields.name: member_limit

fields.desc: Pass true if users joining the chat via the link need to be approved by chat administrators. In this case, member_limit must be 0.
fields.name: creates_join_request

createForumTopic.desc:
Creates a topic in a forum supergroup chat; requires can_manage_topics rights in the supergroup.
Returns object_ptr<ForumTopicInfo>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Name of the topic; 1-128 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Icon of the topic. Icon color must be one of 0x6FB9F0, 0xFFD67E, 0xCB86DB, 0x8EEE98, 0xFF93B2, or 0xFB6F5F. Telegram Premium users can use any custom emoji as topic icon, other users can use only a custom emoji returned by getForumTopicDefaultIcons.
fields.name: icon

createInvoiceLink.desc:
Creates a link for the given invoice; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<HttpUrl>.

fields.desc: Information about the invoice of the type inputMessageInvoice.
fields.name: invoice

createNewBasicGroupChat.desc:
Creates a new basic group and sends a corresponding messageBasicGroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Identifiers of users to be added to the basic group; may be empty to create a basic group without other members.
fields.name: user_ids

fields.desc: Title of the new basic group; 1-128 characters.
fields.name: title

fields.desc: Message auto-delete time value, in seconds; must be from 0 up to 365 * 86400 and be divisible by 86400. If 0, then messages aren't deleted automatically.
fields.name: message_auto_delete_time

createNewSecretChat.desc:
Creates a new secret chat. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the target user.
fields.name: user_id

createNewStickerSet.desc:
Creates a new sticker set. Returns the newly created sticker set.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSet>.

fields.desc: Sticker set owner; ignored for regular users.
fields.name: user_id

fields.desc: Sticker set title; 1-64 characters.
fields.name: title

fields.desc: Sticker set name. Can contain only English letters, digits and underscores. Must end with "by<bot username>" (<bot_username> is case insensitive) for bots; 1-64 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Format of the stickers in the set.
fields.name: sticker_format

fields.desc: Type of the stickers in the set.
fields.name: sticker_type

fields.desc: Pass true if stickers in the sticker set must be repainted; for custom emoji sticker sets only.
fields.name: needs_repainting

fields.desc: List of stickers to be added to the set; must be non-empty. All stickers must have the same format. For TGS stickers, uploadStickerFile must be used before the sticker is shown.
fields.name: stickers

fields.desc: Source of the sticker set; may be empty if unknown.
fields.name: source

createNewSupergroupChat.desc:
Creates a new supergroup or channel and sends a corresponding messageSupergroupChatCreate. Returns the newly created chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Title of the new chat; 1-128 characters.
fields.name: title

fields.desc: Pass true to create a forum supergroup chat.
fields.name: is_forum

fields.desc: Pass true to create a channel chat; ignored if a forum is created.
fields.name: is_channel

fields.desc: Chat description; 0-255 characters.
fields.name: description

fields.desc: Chat location if a location-based supergroup is being created; pass null to create an ordinary supergroup chat.
fields.name: location

fields.desc: Message auto-delete time value, in seconds; must be from 0 up to 365 * 86400 and be divisible by 86400. If 0, then messages aren't deleted automatically.
fields.name: message_auto_delete_time

fields.desc: Pass true to create a supergroup for importing messages using importMessages.
fields.name: for_import

createPrivateChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a given user.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: User identifier.
fields.name: user_id

fields.desc: Pass true to create the chat without a network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.
fields.name: force

createSecretChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known secret chat.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Secret chat identifier.
fields.name: secret_chat_id

createSupergroupChat.desc:
Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Chat>.

fields.desc: Supergroup or channel identifier.
fields.name: supergroup_id

fields.desc: Pass true to create the chat without a network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect.
fields.name: force

createTemporaryPassword.desc:
Creates a new temporary password for processing payments.
Returns object_ptr<TemporaryPasswordState>.

fields.desc: The 2-step verification password of the current user.
fields.name: password

fields.desc: Time during which the temporary password will be valid, in seconds; must be between 60 and 86400.
fields.name: valid_for

createVideoChat.desc:
Creates a video chat (a group call bound to a chat). Available only for basic groups, supergroups and channels; requires can_manage_video_chats rights.
Returns object_ptr<GroupCallId>.

fields.desc: Identifier of a chat in which the video chat will be created.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Group call title; if empty, chat title will be used.
fields.name: title

fields.desc: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the group call is supposed to be started by an administrator; 0 to start the video chat immediately. The date must be at least 10 seconds and at most 8 days in the future.
fields.name: start_date

fields.desc: Pass true to create an RTMP stream instead of an ordinary video chat; requires creator privileges.
fields.name: is_rtmp_stream

deleteAccount.desc:
Deletes the account of the current user, deleting all information associated with the user from the server. The phone number of the account can be used to create a new account. Can be called before authorization when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The reason why the account was deleted; optional.
fields.name: reason

fields.desc: The 2-step verification password of the current user. If not specified, account deletion can be canceled within one week.
fields.name: password

deleteAllCallMessages.desc:
Deletes all call messages.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Pass true to delete the messages for all users.
fields.name: revoke

deleteAllRevokedChatInviteLinks.desc:
Deletes all revoked chat invite links created by a given chat administrator. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: User identifier of a chat administrator, which links will be deleted. Must be an identifier of the current user for non-owner.
fields.name: creator_user_id

deleteChat.desc:
Deletes a chat along with all messages in the corresponding chat for all chat members. For group chats this will release the usernames and remove all members. Use the field chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users to find whether the method can be applied to the chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

deleteChatBackground.desc:
Deletes background in a specific chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Pass true to restore previously set background. Can be used only in private and secret chats with non-deleted users if userFullInfo.set_chat_background == true. Supposed to be used from messageChatSetBackground messages with the currently set background that was set for both sides by the other user.
fields.name: restore_previous

deleteChatFolder.desc:
Deletes existing chat folder.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat folder identifier.
fields.name: chat_folder_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of the chats to leave. The chats must be pinned or always included in the folder.
fields.name: leave_chat_ids

deleteChatFolderInviteLink.desc:
Deletes an invite link for a chat folder.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat folder identifier.
fields.name: chat_folder_id

fields.desc: Invite link to be deleted.
fields.name: invite_link

deleteChatHistory.desc:
Deletes all messages in the chat. Use chat.can_be_deleted_only_for_self and chat.can_be_deleted_for_all_users fields to find whether and how the method can be applied to the chat.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Pass true to remove the chat from all chat lists.
fields.name: remove_from_chat_list

fields.desc: Pass true to delete chat history for all users.
fields.name: revoke

deleteChatMessagesByDate.desc:
Deletes all messages between the specified dates in a chat. Supported only for private chats and basic groups. Messages sent in the last 30 seconds will not be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: The minimum date of the messages to delete.
fields.name: min_date

fields.desc: The maximum date of the messages to delete.
fields.name: max_date

fields.desc: Pass true to delete chat messages for all users; private chats only.
fields.name: revoke

deleteChatMessagesBySender.desc:
Deletes all messages sent by the specified message sender in a chat. Supported only for supergroups; requires can_delete_messages administrator privileges.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the sender of messages to delete.
fields.name: sender_id

deleteChatReplyMarkup.desc:
Deletes the default reply markup from a chat. Must be called after a one-time keyboard or a replyMarkupForceReply reply markup has been used. An updateChatReplyMarkup update will be sent if the reply markup is changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: The message identifier of the used keyboard.
fields.name: message_id

deleteCommands.desc:
Deletes commands supported by the bot for the given user scope and language; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The scope to which the commands are relevant; pass null to delete commands in the default bot command scope.
fields.name: scope

fields.desc: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code or an empty string.
fields.name: language_code

deleteFile.desc:
Deletes a file from the TDLib file cache.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the file to delete.
fields.name: file_id

deleteForumTopic.desc:
Deletes all messages in a forum topic; requires can_delete_messages administrator right in the supergroup unless the user is creator of the topic, the topic has no messages from other users and has at most 11 messages.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Message thread identifier of the forum topic.
fields.name: message_thread_id

deleteLanguagePack.desc:
Deletes all information about a language pack in the current localization target. The language pack which is currently in use (including base language pack) or is being synchronized can't be deleted. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the language pack to delete.
fields.name: language_pack_id

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to be deleted.
fields.name: message_ids

fields.desc: Pass true to delete messages for all chat members. Always true for supergroups, channels and secret chats.
fields.name: revoke

deletePassportElement.desc:
Deletes a Telegram Passport element.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Element type.
fields.name: type

deleteProfilePhoto.desc:
Deletes a profile photo.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the profile photo to delete.
fields.name: profile_photo_id

deleteRevokedChatInviteLink.desc:
Deletes revoked chat invite links. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Invite link to revoke.
fields.name: invite_link

deleteSavedCredentials.desc:
Deletes saved credentials for all payment provider bots.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteSavedOrderInfo.desc:
Deletes saved order information.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

deleteStickerSet.desc:
Deleted a sticker set; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Sticker set name.
fields.name: name

deleteStory.desc:
Deletes a previously sent story. Can be called only if story.can_be_deleted == true.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat that posted the story.
fields.name: story_sender_chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the story to delete.
fields.name: story_id

destroy.desc:
Closes the TDLib instance, destroying all local data without a proper logout. The current user session will remain in the list of all active sessions. All local data will be destroyed. After the destruction completes updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

disableAllSupergroupUsernames.desc:
Disables all active non-editable usernames of a supergroup or channel, requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the supergroup or channel.
fields.name: supergroup_id

disableProxy.desc:
Disables the currently enabled proxy. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Call identifier.
fields.name: call_id

fields.desc: Pass true if the user was disconnected.
fields.name: is_disconnected

fields.desc: The call duration, in seconds.
fields.name: duration

fields.desc: Pass true if the call was a video call.
fields.name: is_video

fields.desc: Identifier of the connection used during the call.
fields.name: connection_id

disconnectAllWebsites.desc:
Disconnects all websites from the current user's Telegram account.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

disconnectWebsite.desc:
Disconnects website from the current user's Telegram account.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Website identifier.
fields.name: website_id

downloadFile.desc:
Downloads a file from the cloud. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates.
Returns object_ptr<File>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the file to download.
fields.name: file_id

fields.desc: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first.
fields.name: priority

fields.desc: The starting position from which the file needs to be downloaded.
fields.name: offset

fields.desc: Number of bytes which need to be downloaded starting from the "offset" position before the download will automatically be canceled; use 0 to download without a limit.
fields.name: limit

fields.desc: Pass true to return response only after the file download has succeeded, has failed, has been canceled, or a new downloadFile request with different offset/limit parameters was sent; pass false to return file state immediately, just after the download has been started.
fields.name: synchronous

editChatFolder.desc:
Edits existing chat folder. Returns information about the edited chat folder.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFolderInfo>.

fields.desc: Chat folder identifier.
fields.name: chat_folder_id

fields.desc: The edited chat folder.
fields.name: folder

editChatFolderInviteLink.desc:
Edits an invite link for a chat folder.
Returns object_ptr<ChatFolderInviteLink>.

fields.desc: Chat folder identifier.
fields.name: chat_folder_id

fields.desc: Invite link to be edited.
fields.name: invite_link

fields.desc: New name of the link; 0-32 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: New identifiers of chats to be accessible by the invite link. Use getChatsForChatFolderInviteLink to get suitable chats. Basic groups will be automatically converted to supergroups before link editing.
fields.name: chat_ids

editChatInviteLink.desc:
Edits a non-primary invite link for a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links.
Returns object_ptr<ChatInviteLink>.

fields.desc: Chat identifier.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Invite link to be edited.
fields.name: invite_link

fields.desc: Invite link name; 0-32 characters.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the link will expire; pass 0 if never.
fields.name: expiration_date

fields.desc: The maximum number of chat members that can join the chat via the link simultaneously; 0-99999; pass 0 if not limited.
fields.name: member_limit

fields.desc: Pass true if users joining the chat via the link need to be approved by chat administrators. In this case, member_limit must be 0.
fields.name: creates_join_request

editCustomLanguagePackInfo.desc:
Edits information about a custom local language pack in the current localization target. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: New information about the custom local language pack.
fields.name: info

editForumTopic.desc:
Edits title and icon of a topic in a forum supergroup chat; requires can_manage_topics administrator right in the supergroup unless the user is creator of the topic.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Message thread identifier of the forum topic.
fields.name: message_thread_id

fields.desc: New name of the topic; 0-128 characters. If empty, the previous topic name is kept.
fields.name: name

fields.desc: Pass true to edit the icon of the topic. Icon of the General topic can't be edited.
fields.name: edit_icon_custom_emoji

fields.desc: Identifier of the new custom emoji for topic icon; pass 0 to remove the custom emoji. Ignored if edit_icon_custom_emoji is false. Telegram Premium users can use any custom emoji, other users can use only a custom emoji returned by getForumTopicDefaultIcons.
fields.name: icon_custom_emoji_id

editInlineMessageCaption.desc:
Edits the caption of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Inline message identifier.
fields.name: inline_message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New message content caption; pass null to remove caption; 0-getOption("message_caption_length_max") characters.
fields.name: caption

editInlineMessageLiveLocation.desc:
Edits the content of a live location in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Inline message identifier.
fields.name: inline_message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New location content of the message; pass null to stop sharing the live location.
fields.name: location

fields.desc: The new direction in which the location moves, in degrees; 1-360. Pass 0 if unknown.
fields.name: heading

fields.desc: The new maximum distance for proximity alerts, in meters (0-100000). Pass 0 if the notification is disabled.
fields.name: proximity_alert_radius

editInlineMessageMedia.desc:
Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video in an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Inline message identifier.
fields.name: inline_message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: inputMessageAnimation, inputMessageAudio, inputMessageDocument, inputMessagePhoto or inputMessageVideo.
fields.name: input_message_content

editInlineMessageReplyMarkup.desc:
Edits the reply markup of an inline message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Inline message identifier.
fields.name: inline_message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_markup

editInlineMessageText.desc:
Edits the text of an inline text or game message sent via a bot; for bots only.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Inline message identifier.
fields.name: inline_message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New text content of the message. Must be of type inputMessageText.
fields.name: input_message_content

editMessageCaption.desc:
Edits the message content caption. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New message content caption; 0-getOption("message_caption_length_max") characters; pass null to remove caption.
fields.name: caption

editMessageLiveLocation.desc:
Edits the message content of a live location. Messages can be edited for a limited period of time specified in the live location. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New location content of the message; pass null to stop sharing the live location.
fields.name: location

fields.desc: The new direction in which the location moves, in degrees; 1-360. Pass 0 if unknown.
fields.name: heading

fields.desc: The new maximum distance for proximity alerts, in meters (0-100000). Pass 0 if the notification is disabled.
fields.name: proximity_alert_radius

editMessageMedia.desc:
Edits the content of a message with an animation, an audio, a document, a photo or a video, including message caption. If only the caption needs to be edited, use editMessageCaption instead. The media can't be edited if the message was set to self-destruct or to a self-destructing media. The type of message content in an album can't be changed with exception of replacing a photo with a video or vice versa. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: inputMessageAnimation, inputMessageAudio, inputMessageDocument, inputMessagePhoto or inputMessageVideo.
fields.name: input_message_content

editMessageReplyMarkup.desc:
Edits the message reply markup; for bots only. Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none.
fields.name: reply_markup

editMessageSchedulingState.desc:
Edits the time when a scheduled message will be sent. Scheduling state of all messages in the same album or forwarded together with the message will be also changed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message scheduling state; pass null to send the message immediately.
fields.name: scheduling_state

editMessageText.desc:
Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side.
Returns object_ptr<Message>.

fields.desc: The chat the message belongs to.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the message.
fields.name: message_id

fields.desc: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only.
fields.name: reply_markup

fields.desc: New text content of the message. Must be of type inputMessageText.
fields.name: input_message_content

editProxy.desc:
Edits an existing proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Proxy>.

fields.desc: Proxy identifier.
fields.name: proxy_id

fields.desc: Proxy server domain or IP address.
fields.name: server

fields.desc: Proxy server port.
fields.name: port

fields.desc: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy.
fields.name: enable

fields.desc: Proxy type.
fields.name: type

editStory.desc:
Changes content and caption of a story. Can be called only if story.can_be_edited == true.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat that posted the story.
fields.name: story_sender_chat_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the story to edit.
fields.name: story_id

fields.desc: New content of the story; pass null to keep the current content.
fields.name: content

fields.desc: New clickable rectangle areas to be shown on the story media; pass null to keep the current areas. Areas can't be edited if story content isn't changed.
fields.name: areas

fields.desc: New story caption; pass null to keep the current caption.
fields.name: caption

enableProxy.desc:
Enables a proxy. Only one proxy can be enabled at a time. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Proxy identifier.
fields.name: proxy_id

endGroupCall.desc:
Ends a group call. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Group call identifier.
fields.name: group_call_id

endGroupCallRecording.desc:
Ends recording of an active group call. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed group call flag.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Group call identifier.
fields.name: group_call_id

endGroupCallScreenSharing.desc:
Ends screen sharing in a joined group call.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: Group call identifier.
fields.name: group_call_id

finishFileGeneration.desc:
Finishes the file generation.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

fields.desc: The identifier of the generation process.
fields.name: generation_id

fields.desc: If passed, the file generation has failed and must be terminated; pass null if the file generation succeeded.
fields.name: error

forwardMessages.desc:
Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat to which to forward messages.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: If not 0, a message thread identifier in which the message will be sent; for forum threads only.
fields.name: message_thread_id

fields.desc: Identifier of the chat from which to forward messages.
fields.name: from_chat_id

fields.desc: Identifiers of the messages to forward. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order. At most 100 messages can be forwarded simultaneously. A message can be forwarded only if message.can_be_forwarded.
fields.name: message_ids

fields.desc: Options to be used to send the messages; pass null to use default options.
fields.name: options

fields.desc: Pass true to copy content of the messages without reference to the original sender. Always true if the messages are forwarded to a secret chat or are local.
fields.name: send_copy

fields.desc: Pass true to remove media captions of message copies. Ignored if send_copy is false.
fields.name: remove_caption

getAccountTtl.desc:
Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted.
Returns object_ptr<AccountTtl>.

getActiveLiveLocationMessages.desc:
Returns all active live locations that need to be updated by the application. The list is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

getActiveSessions.desc:
Returns all active sessions of the current user.
Returns object_ptr<Sessions>.

getAllPassportElements.desc:
Returns all available Telegram Passport elements.
Returns object_ptr<PassportElements>.

fields.desc: The 2-step verification password of the current user.
fields.name: password

getAllStickerEmojis.desc:
Returns unique emoji that correspond to stickers to be found by the getStickers(sticker_type, query, 1000000, chat_id).
Returns object_ptr<Emojis>.

fields.desc: Type of the stickers to search for.
fields.name: sticker_type

fields.desc: Search query.
fields.name: query

fields.desc: Chat identifier for which to find stickers.
fields.name: chat_id

fields.desc: Pass true if only main emoji for each found sticker must be included in the result.
fields.name: return_only_main_emoji

getAnimatedEmoji.desc:
Returns an animated emoji corresponding to a given emoji. Returns a 404 error if the emoji has no animated emoji.
Returns object_ptr<AnimatedEmoji>.

fields.desc: The emoji.
fields.name: emoji

getApplicationConfig.desc:
Returns application config, provided by the server. Can be called before authorization.
Returns object_ptr<JsonValue>.

getApplicationDownloadLink.desc:
Returns the link for downloading official Telegram application to be used when the current user invites friends to Telegram.
Returns object_ptr<HttpUrl>.

getArchiveChatListSettings.desc:
Returns settings for automatic moving of chats to and from the Archive chat lists.
Returns object_ptr<ArchiveChatListSettings>.

getArchivedStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of archived sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

fields.desc: Type of the sticker sets to return.
fields.name: sticker_type

fields.desc: Identifier of the sticker set from which to return the result.
fields.name: offset_sticker_set_id

fields.desc: The maximum number of sticker sets to return; up to 100.
fields.name: limit

getAttachedStickerSets.desc:
Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file, including regular, mask, and emoji sticker sets. Currently, only animations, photos, and videos can have attached sticker sets.
Returns object_ptr<StickerSets>.

fields.desc: File identifier.
fields.name: file_id

getAttachmentMenuBot.desc:
Returns information about a bot that can be added to attachment or side menu.
Returns object_ptr<AttachmentMenuBot>.

fields.desc: Bot's user identifier.
fields.name: bot_user_id

getAuthorizationState.desc:
Returns the current authorization state; this is an offline request. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state. Can be called before initialization.

getAutoDownloadSettingsPresets.desc:

requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery.desc:
Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword.
Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

Returns object_ptr<EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeInfo>.

requestQrCodeAuthentication.desc:
Requests QR code authentication by scanning a QR code on another logged in device. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber, or if there is no pending authentication query and the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress, authorizationStateWaitEmailCode, authorizationStateWaitCode, authorizationStateWaitRegistration, or authorizationStateWaitPassword.

Returns object_ptr<Ok>.

Resends the authentication code sent to confirm a new phone number for the current user. Works only if the previously received authenticationCodeInfo next_code_type was not null and the server-specified timeout has passed.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resendEmailAddressVerificationCode.desc:
Resends the code to verify an email address to be added to a user's Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resendLoginEmailAddressCode.desc:
Resends the login email address verification code.
Returns object_ptr<EmailAddressAuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resendMessages.desc:
Resends messages which failed to send. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed. If a message is re-sent, the corresponding failed to send message is deleted. Returns the sent messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be re-sent, null will be returned instead of the message.
Returns object_ptr<Messages>.

fields.name: quote

resendPhoneNumberConfirmationCode.desc:
Resends phone number confirmation code.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resendPhoneNumberVerificationCode.desc:
Resends the code to verify a phone number to be added to a user's Telegram Passport.
Returns object_ptr<AuthenticationCodeInfo>.

resendRecoveryEmailAddressCode.desc:
Resends the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code.
Returns object_ptr<PasswordState>.

resetAllNotificationSettings.desc:

resetNetworkStatistics.desc:

Removes 2-step verification password without previous password and access to recovery email address. The password can't be reset immediately and the request needs to be repeated after the specified time.

For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit. AuthenticationCodeType.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Provides information about the method by which an authentication code is delivered to the user.

authenticationCodeTypeCall.desc: An authentication code is delivered via a phone call to the specified phone number.

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseAndroid.desc: An authentication code is delivered via Firebase Authentication to the official Android application.

fields.desc: Nonce to pass to the SafetyNet Attestation API.
fields.name: nonce

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseIos.desc: An authentication code is delivered via Firebase Authentication to the official iOS application.

fields.desc: Receipt of successful application token validation to compare with receipt from push notification.
fields.name: receipt

fields.desc: Time after the next authentication method is supposed to be used if verification push notification isn't received, in seconds.
fields.name: push_timeout

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeFlashCall.desc: An authentication code is delivered by an immediately canceled call to the specified phone number. The phone number that calls is the code that must be entered automatically.

fields.desc: Pattern of the phone number from which the call will be made.
fields.name: pattern

authenticationCodeTypeFragment.desc: An authentication code is delivered to https://fragment.com. The user must be logged in there via a wallet owning the phone number's NFT.

fields.desc: URL to open to receive the code.
fields.name: url

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeMissedCall.desc: An authentication code is delivered by an immediately canceled call to the specified phone number. The last digits of the phone number that calls are the code that must be entered manually by the user.

fields.desc: Prefix of the phone number from which the call will be made.
fields.name: phone_number_prefix

fields.desc: Number of digits in the code, excluding the prefix.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeSms.desc: An authentication code is delivered via an SMS message to the specified phone number; applications may not receive this type of code.

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

authenticationCodeTypeTelegramMessage.desc: An authentication code is delivered via a private Telegram message, which can be viewed from another active session.

fields.desc: Length of the code.
fields.name: length

AuthorizationState.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Represents the current authorization state of the TDLib client.

authorizationStateClosed.desc: TDLib client is in its final state. All databases are closed and all resources are released. No other updates will be received after this. All queries will be responded to with error code 500. To continue working, one must create a new instance of the TDLib client.

authorizationStateClosing.desc: TDLib is closing, all subsequent queries will be answered with the error 500. Note that closing TDLib can take a while. All resources will be freed only after authorizationStateClosed has been received.

authorizationStateLoggingOut.desc: The user is currently logging out.

authorizationStateReady.desc: The user has been successfully authorized. TDLib is now ready to answer general requests.

authorizationStateWaitCode.desc: TDLib needs the user's authentication code to authorize. Call checkAuthenticationCode to check the code.

fields.desc: Information about the authorization code that was sent.
fields.name: code_info

authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress.desc: TDLib needs the user's email address to authorize. Call setAuthenticationEmailAddress to provide the email address, or directly call checkAuthenticationEmailCode with Apple ID/Google ID token if allowed.

fields.desc: True, if authorization through Apple ID is allowed.
fields.name: allow_apple_id

fields.desc: True, if authorization through Google ID is allowed.
fields.name: allow_google_id

authorizationStateWaitEmailCode.desc: TDLib needs the user's authentication code sent to an email address to authorize. Call checkAuthenticationEmailCode to provide the code.

fields.desc: True, if authorization through Apple ID is allowed.
fields.name: allow_apple_id

fields.desc: True, if authorization through Google ID is allowed.
fields.name: allow_google_id

fields.desc: Information about the sent authentication code.
fields.name: code_info

fields.desc: Reset state of the email address; may be null if the email address can't be reset.
fields.name: email_address_reset_state

authorizationStateWaitOtherDeviceConfirm.desc: The user needs to confirm authorization on another logged in device by scanning a QR code with the provided link.

fields.desc: A tg:// URL for the QR code. The link will be updated frequently.
fields.name: link

authorizationStateWaitPassword.desc: The user has been authorized, but needs to enter a 2-step verification password to start using the application. Call checkAuthenticationPassword to provide the password, or requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery to recover the password, or deleteAccount to delete the account after a week.

fields.desc: Hint for the password; may be empty.
fields.name: password_hint

fields.desc: True, if a recovery email address has been set up.
fields.name: has_recovery_email_address

fields.desc: True, if some Telegram Passport elements were saved.
fields.name: has_passport_data

fields.desc: Pattern of the email address to which the recovery email was sent; empty until a recovery email has been sent.
fields.name: recovery_email_address_pattern

authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber.desc: TDLib needs the user's phone number to authorize. Call setAuthenticationPhoneNumber to provide the phone number, or use requestQrCodeAuthentication or checkAuthenticationBotToken for other authentication options.

authorizationStateWaitRegistration.desc: The user is unregistered and need to accept terms of service and enter their first name and last name to finish registration. Call registerUser to accept the terms of service and provide the data.

fields.desc: Telegram terms of service.
fields.name: terms_of_service

authorizationStateWaitTdlibParameters.desc: Initialization parameters are needed. Call setTdlibParameters to provide them.

AutosaveSettingsScope.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes scope of autosave settings.

autosaveSettingsScopeChat.desc: Autosave settings applied to a chat.

autosaveSettingsScopeGroupChats.desc: Autosave settings applied to all basic group and supergroup chats without chat-specific settings.

autosaveSettingsScopePrivateChats.desc: Autosave settings applied to all private chats without chat-specific settings.

BackgroundFill.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes a fill of a background.

backgroundFillFreeformGradient.desc: Describes a freeform gradient fill of a background.

backgroundFillGradient.desc: Describes a gradient fill of a background.

fields.desc: A bottom color of the background in the RGB24 format.

fields.name: rotation_angle

backgroundFillSolid.desc: Describes a solid fill of a background.

fields.desc: A color of the background in the RGB24 format.
fields.name: color

BackgroundType.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the type of a background.

fields.desc: The background fill.
fields.name: fill

backgroundTypePattern.desc: A PNG or TGV (gzipped subset of SVG with MIME type "application/x-tgwallpattern") pattern to be combined with the background fill chosen by the user.

fields.desc: Intensity of the pattern when it is shown above the filled background; 0-100.

fields.desc: True, if the background fill must be applied only to the pattern itself. All other pixels are black in this case. For dark themes only.

fields.desc: True, if the background needs to be slightly moved when device is tilted.
fields.name: is_moving

fields.desc: True, if the wallpaper must be downscaled to fit in 450x450 square and then box-blurred with radius 12.
fields.name: is_blurred

fields.desc: True, if the background needs to be slightly moved when device is tilted.
fields.name: is_moving

BlockList.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes a type of a block list.

blockListMain.desc: The main block list that disallows writing messages to the current user, receiving their status and photo, viewing of stories, and some other actions.

blockListStories.desc: The block list that disallows viewing of stories of the current user.

BotCommandScope.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Represents the scope to which bot commands are relevant.

botCommandScopeAllChatAdministrators.desc: A scope covering all group and supergroup chat administrators.

botCommandScopeChatAdministrators.desc: A scope covering all administrators of a chat.

botCommandScopeChatMember.desc: A scope covering a member of a chat.

fields.name: user_id

BotWriteAccessAllowReason.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes a reason why a bot was allowed to write messages to the current user.

botWriteAccessAllowReasonAcceptedRequest.desc: The user accepted bot's request to send messages with allowBotToSendMessages.

botWriteAccessAllowReasonAddedToAttachme.desc: The user added the bot to attachment or side menu using toggleBotIsAddedToAttachmentMenu.

botWriteAccessAllowReasonConnectedWebsit.desc: The user connected a website by logging in using Telegram Login Widget on it.

botWriteAccessAllowReasonLaunchedWebApp.desc: The user launched a Web App using getWebAppLinkUrl.

fields.desc: Information about the Web App.
fields.name: web_app

CallDiscardReason.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the reason why a call was discarded.

callDiscardReasonDeclined.desc: The call was ended before the conversation started. It was declined by the other party.

callDiscardReasonDisconnected.desc: The call was ended during the conversation because the users were disconnected.

callDiscardReasonEmpty.desc: The call wasn't discarded, or the reason is unknown.

callDiscardReasonHungUp.desc: The call was ended because one of the parties hung up.

callDiscardReasonMissed.desc: The call was ended before the conversation started. It was canceled by the caller or missed by the other party.

CallProblem.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the exact type of a problem with a call.

callProblemEcho.desc: The user heard their own voice.

callProblemSilentLocal.desc: The user couldn't hear the other side.

callProblemSilentRemote.desc: The other side couldn't hear the user.

CallServerType.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the type of a call server.

fields.desc: A peer tag to be used with the reflector.
fields.name: peer_tag

fields.desc: True, if the server uses TCP instead of UDP.
fields.name: is_tcp

fields.desc: Username to be used for authentication.
fields.name: username

fields.desc: Authentication password.
fields.name: password

fields.desc: True, if the server supports TURN.
fields.name: supports_turn

fields.desc: True, if the server supports STUN.
fields.name: supports_stun

CallState.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the current call state.

fields.desc: The reason why the call has ended.
fields.name: reason

fields.desc: True, if the call rating must be sent to the server.
fields.name: need_rating

fields.desc: True, if the call debug information must be sent to the server.
fields.name: need_debug_information

fields.desc: True, if the call log must be sent to the server.
fields.name: need_log

callStateError.desc: The call has ended with an error.

fields.desc: Error. An error with the code 4005000 will be returned if an outgoing call is missed because of an expired timeout.
fields.name: error

callStateExchangingKeys.desc: The call has been answered and encryption keys are being exchanged.

callStateHangingUp.desc: The call is hanging up after discardCall has been called.

callStatePending.desc: The call is pending, waiting to be accepted by a user.

fields.desc: True, if the call has already been created by the server.
fields.name: is_created

fields.desc: True, if the call has already been received by the other party.
fields.name: is_received

callStateReady.desc: The call is ready to use.

fields.desc: Call protocols supported by the other call participant.
fields.name: protocol

fields.desc: List of available call servers.
fields.name: servers

fields.desc: A JSON-encoded call config.
fields.name: config

fields.desc: Call encryption key.
fields.name: encryption_key

fields.desc: Encryption key emojis fingerprint.
fields.name: emojis

fields.desc: True, if peer-to-peer connection is allowed by users privacy settings.
fields.name: allow_p2p

CallbackQueryPayload.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Represents a payload of a callback query.

callbackQueryPayloadData.desc: The payload for a general callback button.

fields.name: data

callbackQueryPayloadDataWithPassword.desc: The payload for a callback button requiring password.

fields.desc: The 2-step verification password for the current user.
fields.name: password

fields.desc: Data that was attached to the callback button.
fields.name: data

callbackQueryPayloadGame.desc: The payload for a game callback button.

fields.desc: A short name of the game that was attached to the callback button.
fields.name: game_short_name

CanSendStoryResult.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Represents result of checking whether the current user can send a story in the specific chat.

canSendStoryResultActiveStoryLimitExceed.desc: The limit for the number of active stories exceeded. The user can buy Telegram Premium, delete an active story, or wait for the oldest story to expire.

canSendStoryResultBoostNeeded.desc: The channel chat must be boosted first by Telegram Premium subscribers to post more stories. Call getChatBoostStatus to get current boost status of the chat.

canSendStoryResultMonthlyLimitExceeded.desc: The monthly limit for the number of posted stories exceeded. The user needs to buy Telegram Premium or wait specified time.

fields.desc: Time left before the user can send the next story.
fields.name: retry_after

canSendStoryResultPremiumNeeded.desc: The user must subscribe to Telegram Premium to be able to post stories.

canSendStoryResultWeeklyLimitExceeded.desc: The weekly limit for the number of posted stories exceeded. The user needs to buy Telegram Premium or wait specified time.

fields.desc: Time left before the user can send the next story.
fields.name: retry_after

CanTransferOwnershipResult.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Represents result of checking whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user.

canTransferOwnershipResultPasswordNeeded.desc: The 2-step verification needs to be enabled first.

canTransferOwnershipResultPasswordTooFre.desc: The 2-step verification was enabled recently, user needs to wait.

fields.name: retry_after

canTransferOwnershipResultSessionTooFres.desc: The session was created recently, user needs to wait.

fields.desc: Time left before the session can be used to transfer ownership of a chat, in seconds.
fields.name: retry_after

ChatAction.desc: This class is an abstract base class. Describes the different types of activity in a chat.

chatActionCancel.desc: The user has canceled the previous action.

chatActionChoosingContact.desc: The user is picking a contact to send.

chatActionChoosingLocation.desc: The user is picking a location or venue to send.

chatActionChoosingSticker.desc: The user is picking a sticker to send.

chatActionRecordingVideo.desc: The user is recording a video.

chatActionRecordingVideoNote.desc: The user is recording a video note.

chatActionRecordingVoiceNote.desc: The user is recording a voice note.

chatActionStartPlayingGame.desc: The user has started to play a game.

chatActionTyping.desc: The user is typing a message.

chatActionUploadingDocument.desc: The user is uploading a document.

chatActionUploadingPhoto.desc: The user is uploading a photo.

chatActionUploadingVideo.desc: The user is uploading a video.

chatActionUploadingVideoNote.desc: The user is uploading a video note.

chatActionUploadingVoiceNote.desc: The user is uploading a voice note.

chatActionWatchingAnimations.desc: The user is watching animations sent by the other party by clicking on an animated emoji.
